openvpn (2.7~rc3-debian0) stable; urgency=medium

  * OpenVPN Release 2.7_rc3 (Gert Doering, 31ef3d66)
  * interactive.c: harden pipe handling against misbehaving clients (Lev Stipakov, 6088451b)
  * dco: process messages immediately after read (Ralf Lici, 7791f535)
  * Remove remainders of --no-name-remapping option (Gert Doering, 0effd6ca)
  * extract_x509_field_ssl(): verify that X509_NAME is not NULL. (Gert Doering, f18e3141)
  * configure/CMake: Unify Windows handling (Frank Lichtenheld, afdf0028)
  * configure/CMake: Remove unused checks (Frank Lichtenheld, e52f03d4)
  * Linux: Assume we have a kernel that was release in the last 15 years (Frank Lichtenheld, 2abfb759)
  * error: Allow status argument to check_status to be ssize_t (Frank Lichtenheld, ea2f8ef6)
  * Changes.rst: Fix various syntax errors and typos (Frank Lichtenheld, 123cc9a0)
  * Change '--multihome' behaviour regarding egress interface selection. (Gert Doering, eeb866ac)
  * iservice: rename one_glyph to glyph_size (Heiko Hund, dd1524c0)
  * iservice: fix off by one error (Heiko Hund, dc5baf80)
  * iservice: handle ignoring itf domains correctly (Heiko Hund, c0cb5102)
  * iservice: return correct size when domains are truncated (Heiko Hund, aeda359e)
  * iservice: fix calculation of converted domains size (Heiko Hund, ac6c9d65)
  * multi-socket: do not return tuntap flags on server-side (Gianmarco De Gregori, 6244e466)
  * Restrict access to the service pipe to SYSTEM and owner (Selva Nair, 0a429cb1)
  * Harden interactive service pipe (Selva Nair, 05d0808e)
  * iservice: check for NULL pointer (Heiko Hund, 2e2ac94e)
  * iservice: make sure registry string is terminated (Heiko Hund, a1c41b0a)
  * iservice: make sure buffer size is not zero (Heiko Hund, c20a960a)
  * multi-socket: remove duplicated/dead code (Gianmarco De Gregori, 779ab39d)
  * iservice: fix buffer size in call to FormatMessage (Heiko Hund, b39bed53)
  * tls_crypt: Fix Coverity complaint in tls_crypt_v2_check_client_key_age (Frank Lichtenheld, 2969837a)
  * GHA: Add macos-26 and remove OpenSSL 1.1 builds on macOS (Frank Lichtenheld, 98077190)
  * Add option to check tls-crypt-v2 key timestamps (Max Fillinger, 20b234b2)
  * GHA: Maintenance update November 2025 (Frank Lichtenheld, 92eaedbe)
  * doc: Document potential filesystem pitfalls of client-config-dir (Frank Lichtenheld, 8d278223)
  * route: handle default gateway (net_gateway) and nexthop towards VPN server separately (Marco Baffo, 2777cdd3)
  * vcpkg-ports/pkcs11-helper: bump version to 1.31 (Selva Nair, 3d0d4b1c)

